  <intro_text filename="flow.swf">
    <![CDATA[<p>Voltage is the electrical push or pressure that causes electrically charged particles to flow through a circuit. Electric current is the flow of electrically charged particles through a circuit. Electrical resistance is the opposition of a material or device to the flow of electric current.<br /><br />A water system makes a good analogy to electricity.<br /><br />Voltage corresponds to the water pressure.<br /><br />Current corresponds to the water flow.<br /><br />Resistance corresponds to restrictions in the pipe that slow the flow.<br /><br />Notice that in this simple circuit, the current is the same everywhere.</p>]]>
